# xtgeoip .gitignore
# Rust project. Merged from a general-purpose template; Python-ecosystem and
# audio-project (cdda2img) entries trimmed as not applicable here.

# Rust build artifacts
/target
**/*.rs.bk

# Cargo.lock: xtgeoip is a binary crate — keep it TRACKED for reproducible
# builds, overriding the broad *.lock rule below.
*.lock
!Cargo.lock

# Editor swap / backup files
*.swp
*.swo
*~
*.bak
*.old
*.new
*.orig

# Compiled / binary objects
*.o
*.so
*.exe
*.dll

# Archives (unpack and commit raw sources instead)
*.7z
*.dmg
*.gz
*.iso
*.jar
*.rar
*.tar
*.zip

# Logs and databases
*.log
*.sql
*.sqlite

# Build / run debug + packaging leftovers
*.debug
*.manifest

# Private / personal documentation
*.pdf

# Personal local config (not project-relevant)
*.fish
*.vimrc

# Local working directories (not for sharing).
# /backups holds the tarball archives created by scripts/backup.py.
# NOTE: /extra is NOT ignored — it holds tracked packaging assets (dkms, ufw).
/bak
/backups
/private
/scripts

# Machine-local Claude Code context (committed CLAUDE.md is NOT ignored)
.claude/
CLAUDE.local.md
claude-prompt-*.md

# OS-generated files
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db

# Exceptions: /extra holds curated, tracked packaging assets. Protect them from
# the broad archive/extension globs above (e.g. the committed dkms tarball).
!/extra/**
